            "hide_admin": 0,
            "message": "<h3>Welcome to PostPlanPro<\/h3>\r\n\r\nThis plugin is used to schedule posts \/ media to social platforms.\r\n\r\n<h3>Prerequisites<\/h3>\r\n\r\n1. Wordpress\r\n2. ACF Pro (Needs pro features - repeater)\r\n3. Make.com Scenario\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>Intro<\/h3>\r\n\r\nThis plugin is actually two parts in one. \r\n\r\nThe main part, the 'releases' are used to generate content for social platforms based on a template. \r\nThe release is scheduled on a specific timeframe and will publish itself when that date\/time is in the past.\r\n\r\nThe second plugin (postplanpro_ffmpeg), the scriptflow configs, is a special control and trigger for a github action. That action will take the config and \r\nprogrammatically generate a video to be used in a release. \r\nOnce the video is created the github action will call the wordpress REST API to generate a new release using the location of the new video it created and assign it to the specified config schedule.\r\n\r\nUsing these two plugins it is possible to auto-generate a complete social media presence with scheduled posts containing unique videos.\r\n\r\nOnce the release is published, a webhook is sent to Make.com with all of the content generated. A Make.com scenario will then be triggered and use the data to publish to all the social platforms.\r\n\r\n<h3>Curl Create \/ Update<\/h3>\r\nMake sure the URL for the POST Target is <code>https:\/\/localhost:8443\/wp-json\/custom\/v1\/release<\/code> replacing localhost:port withyour own domain.\r\n\r\n<h3>Workflow<\/h3>\r\n\r\nSee the diagram below for a visual representation of how the system works.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"\/wp-content\/plugins\/wp-plugin__postplanpro\/src\/help\/workflow_new.png\" style=\"width:100%\" >",
            "new_lines": "wpautop",
            "esc_html": 0
        }
